article.headline: Evansville 63, Indiana State 59
article.story: ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Lucious Wagner made a 3-pointer with 42 seconds left and Matt Webster added two free throws with 16 seconds remaining, lifting Evansville to a 63-59 victory over Indiana State in a play-in game Friday in the Missouri Valley Conference Tournament. Ninth-seeded Evansville (7-21) won for just the second time in its last seven games and will face top-seeded Southern Illinois at 12:05 p.m. Saturday. No. 15 Southern Illinois (24-3) won both regular season games. Webster tied a career high with 17 points and a grabbed a career-high 11 rebounds. Andre Burton added 13 and Clint Cuffle 11 for Evansville. The Purple Aces shot 53 percent from the floor. Evansville outrebounded Indiana State 37-22 but made 16 turnovers to just six for the Sycamores. Wilfred Antoine led Indiana State (9-19) with 19 points. Eric Gray added 11. Indiana State defeated Evansville in both regular-season meetings, but lost 12 of its last 13 games. Evansville built a 40-28 lead with 18:47 to play. A 15-4 run helped Indiana State pull within a point at 44-43 at the 13:17 mark. The Purple Aces built the lead back to seven at 52-45 before Indiana State went on an 8-0 run to go ahead 53-52. The teams then traded leads four times before Evansville went up 61-59 on Wagner's 3-pointer from the deep right corner.
